        <div class="bodysection">
            <div class="body" itemprop="about" data-fieldname="body" data-bind="htmlValue:body"><p><strong>The second funniest film ever made! The crown jewel of team Zucker-Abrahams-Zucker's ZAZ-comedies takes you to the wildest flight ever made! The writing, delivery, Leslie Nielsen, Lloyd Bridges and overall surreal craziness just takes over; A true work of genius! This Cpt. Oveur Over.</strong></p>
<p>‘Airplane!’ is the movie that brought the Zucker Brothers and Jim Abrahams into the mainstream of American cinema, introducing their surreal take on classic film to millions.</p>
<p>When food poisoning strikes on an airliner, disturbed ex-pilot Ted Striker (Robert Hayes) must face his demons to bring down the plane safely. And hilariously.</p>
<p><img height="200" src="/static/img/import/airplane_2.jpg?origsrc=http://www.celluloidheroreviews.com/images/airplane_2.jpg" width="353" />From the outset, <em>Airplane! </em>takes no prisoners – any movie, big or small, from Jaws to Flight Into Danger, is fair game to the Zucker / Abrahams team, and they are clearly lovers of the films they parody.</p>
<p>The gags come thick and fast, ranging from deceptively simple wordplay to fantastic visual comedy, and the cast plays it with a pitch-perfect lack of irony. In fact, the casting of disaster movie legends alongside more bizarre choices (Kareem Abdul Jabbar?) lends the movie an added layer of hilarity.</p>



<p><strong></strong></p></div>
